node.text: The summer before senior year is a great time to start working on college application essays. Find more tips on BigFuture.collegeboard.org/get-in/essays.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The College Board on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'COLLEGE APPLICATION ESSAY TIPS'.
Photo by The College Board on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BE PERSONAL Choose a topic that will highlight something about you not covered in other parts of the application.'.

Photo by The College Board on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'OPEN STRONG Open with a strong paragraph that captures the reader's interest and makes them curious about what you'll say next.'.
Photo by The College Board on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BE DIRECT Admissions officers want to see that you can give a direct answer to the essay question.'.
Photo by The College Board on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'MAKE A POINT Your essay should have a comprehensive argument or narrative. Make your point and stick to it.'.

Photo by The College Board on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BE SPECIFIC Share specific details, examples, and reasons to develop your ideas. Instead of saying, "I'm a leader," describe a scenario in which you acted as a leader.'.

Photo by The College Board on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'STICK TO YOUR STYLE Your style should be comfortable for you to write in. Don't overuse the thesaurus to sound impressive.'.
Photo by The College Board on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BE AUTHENTIC Don't try to write what you think colleges are looking for. Be yourself and showcase who you are!'.

Photo by The College Board on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'PROOFREAD Correct grammar, punctuation, and spelling are essential. Ask a teacher, parent, or friend to proofread your essay, too.'.
Photo by The College Board on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'KEEP TRACK OF LENGTH Admissions officers value succinctness. Pay attention to the recommended essay length.'.
